name: Use functional components with hooks
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: Class components or components without hooks
then: Convert to functional components using useState, useEffect, useCallback
why: Functional components with hooks are the modern React pattern and provide better performance and readability.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx", "frontend/src/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use TypeScript for all React components
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: JavaScript files (.js) or components without type annotations
then: Use TypeScript (.tsx) with proper interfaces and type annotations
why: TypeScript provides type safety, better IDE support, and catches errors at compile time.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.tsx", "frontend/src/**/*.ts"]

---
name: Use centralized API hooks instead of direct fetch
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: Direct fetch() calls in components or local API state management
then: Use centralized hooks like useFunds(), useCreateFund(), useEntities()
why: Centralized API integration provides consistent error handling, loading states, and reduces code duplication.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement loading states for async operations
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Components without loading indicators for data fetching
then: Add loading states using CircularProgress or skeleton components
why: Loading states improve user experience by providing feedback during async operations.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use Material-UI components for consistency
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Custom HTML elements or inconsistent UI components
then: Use Material-UI components like Box, Card, TextField, Button
why: Material-UI provides consistent design system and reduces UI development time.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Add form reset logic for modals
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Modal components that don't reset form state when opened
then: Add useEffect with [open] dependency to reset form data
why: Prevents form state persistence between modal opens and improves user experience.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use proper TypeScript interfaces for API data
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Components using 'any' type or missing type annotations
then: Import and use proper interfaces from types/api.ts
why: Type safety prevents runtime errors and improves code maintainability.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Handle type coercion for form data
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Form data used directly without type conversion
then: Convert string form data to proper types (e.g., FundType enum)
why: Form data comes as strings but API expects typed enums and numbers.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement proper error boundaries
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Components without error handling for API failures
then: Add error states with user-friendly messages using Alert component
why: Graceful error handling improves user experience and debugging.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Add form validation with user-friendly messages
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Forms without validation or generic error messages
then: Implement field-level validation with specific error messages
why: Clear validation feedback helps users understand and fix input errors.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Test components with React Testing Library
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: info
if: Components without tests or using enzyme
then: Write tests using React Testing Library with render, screen, fireEvent
why: React Testing Library promotes testing user behavior rather than implementation details.
globs: ["frontend/src/**/*.test.tsx", "frontend/src/**/*.spec.tsx"]

---
name: Use null-safe operators for optional data
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Direct access to potentially undefined data like `funds.map()`
then: Use optional chaining: `funds?.map()` or provide fallbacks
why: Prevents runtime errors when data is still loading or undefined.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Implement proper component props interfaces
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: warning
if: Components without proper prop type definitions
then: Define interfaces for component props with required/optional fields
why: TypeScript interfaces provide better IDE support and catch prop errors early.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]

---
name: Use centralized TypeScript interfaces
scope: typescript
language: typescript
severity: error
if: Local interface definitions that duplicate centralized types
then: Import and use interfaces from types/api.ts
why: Centralized types ensure consistency and reduce maintenance overhead.
globs: ["frontend/src/components/**/*.tsx"]
